vant dates possibly extracted from large portions of document using\\nlong context window models e.g. Gemini or Claude)\\n\\n-  Query Rewriting (entity extraction with GLiner and rewriting with the help of Instructor).\\n\\nIdentifying whether the question can be answered with summaries or full document\\nsearch is required.\\n\\n-  LanceDB\\n\\n-  Metadata Pre-filtering\\n\\n-  Hybrid Search (Full-text Search + Vector Search)\\n\\n-  Neo4j\\n\\n-  KG Search\\n\\n\\n-----\\n\\nCombining LancDB + KG results before Reranker\\n\\nLanceDB\\n\\n-  Reranking with ColBert\\n\\nPossibly Fine-tuning Reranker Colbert Model\\n\\nContext Relevance + Answer Relevance\\n\\nNeo4j GraphRAG for citations + Groundedness checking\\n\\nAgentic Flow (Corrective RAG)\\n\\nEvals with synthetic data and direct or indirect feedback mechanism (clustering of topics\\n\\nand similarity scores etc.)\\nFront end in FastHTML\\n\\n\\n-----\\n\\n', chunks=[MarkdownChunk(name='RAG_pipeline.docx', index=0, text='1 . Basic RAG pipeline -  Google Embedding or some HF Embedding trained on large QnA or Instruction datasets -  Chunking strategy (chunk size + overlap numbers) -  Summarization strategy, for example, book chapter summaries indexed separately or put in KG . -  Metadata creation (e.g . document name, document type, tags and key terms, creation date, any other relevant dates possibly extracted from large portions of document using long context window models e.g . Gemini or Claude) -  Query Rewriting (entity extraction with GLiner and rewriting with the help of Instructor) . Identifying whether the question can be answered with summaries or full document search is required . -  LanceDB -  Metadata Pre-filtering -  Hybrid Search (Full-text Search + Vector Search) -  Reranking with ColBert', metadata={}), MarkdownChunk(name='RAG_pipeline.docx', index=1, text=' full document search is required . -  LanceDB -  Metadata Pre-filtering -  Hybrid Search (Full-text Search + Vector Search) -  Reranking with ColBert -  Check Context Relevance + Answer Relevance (RAGAS or True -  Neo4j GraphRAG for citations + Groundedness checking (convert rewritten Query to Cypher) -  Agentic Flow (Corrective RAG) with Burr -  Logging mechanism (LogFire) or OpenTelemtry with Burr -  Console logging (logging module) -  Evals with synthetic data and direct or indirect feedback mechanism (clustering of topics and similarity scores etc.) -  Front end in FastHTML 2 . Advanced Use case specific and customized RAG pipeline -  Google Embedding or some HF Embedding trained on large QnA or Instruction datasets -  Fine-tuned Embedding Model -  Topic classifier and Query Router', metadata={}), MarkdownChunk(name='RAG_pipeline.docx', index=2, text=' Google Embedding or some HF Embedding trained on large QnA or Instruction datasets -  Fine-tuned Embedding Model -  Topic classifier and Query Router -  Query Rewriting (entity extraction with GLiner and rewriting with the help of Instructor) -  Chunking strategy (chunk size + overlap numbers) -  Summarization strategy, for example, book chapter summaries indexed separately or put in KG . -  Metadata creation (e.g . document name, document type, tags and key terms, creation date, any other relevant dates possibly extracted from large portions of document using long context window models e.g . Gemini or Claude) -  Query Rewriting (entity extraction with GLiner and rewriting with the help of Instructor) . Identifying whether the question can be answered with summaries or full document', metadata={}), MarkdownChunk(name='RAG_pipeline.docx', index=3, text='y extraction with GLiner and rewriting with the help of Instructor) . Identifying whether the question can be answered with summaries or full document search is required . -  LanceDB -  Metadata Pre-filtering -  Hybrid Search (Full-text Search + Vector Search) -  Neo4j -  KG Search --- -- Combining LancDB + KG results before Reranker LanceDB -  Reranking with ColBert Possibly Fine-tuning Reranker Colbe